\nArmstrong is a town in Bryan County, Oklahoma, United States, along the Blue River. The population was 105 at the 2010 census, a 25.2 percent decrease from 141 at the 2000 census.CensusViewer:Armstrong, Oklahoma Population.{http://censusviewer.com/city/OK/Armstrong} The was named for Frank C. Armstrong, a member of the Dawes Commission.O'Dell, Larry. Encyclopedia of Oklahoma History and Culture. \Armstrong.\" Retrieved January 8